WEBVTT

00:03.125 --> 00:05.708
THAT PLACE WAS
SO NICE, PACE.

00:05.708 --> 00:07.875
THEY HAD INDIVIDUAL
TOWELS IN THE BATHROOM.

00:07.875 --> 00:08.834
REALLY?

00:08.834 --> 00:11.750
LAID OUT IN BASKETS
AND EVERYTHING?
MM-HMM.

00:11.750 --> 00:13.667
WELL, IF THAT'S
NOT THE HALLMARK
OF A CLASSY JOINT,

00:13.667 --> 00:14.667
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IS.

00:14.667 --> 00:16.332
WELL, YOU DO
DEFINITELY KNOW

00:16.332 --> 00:17.834
HOW TO TREAT A LADY.

00:17.834 --> 00:20.041
WELL, I GOTTA
SPEND MY MONEY
ON SOMETHIN'.

00:21.208 --> 00:23.333
OH, THAT CAME OUT
TOTALLY WRONG.

00:23.333 --> 00:24.208
BECAUSE YOU ARE NOT--

00:24.208 --> 00:26.667
N-NOT SOMETHING THAT
I JUST SPEND MONEY ON.

00:26.667 --> 00:28.166
IT'S NOT LIKE
A POSSESSION--
BUT I WOULD.

00:28.166 --> 00:29.000
I WOULD, AND I DO.

00:29.000 --> 00:31.250
WELL, WHY DO YOU THINK
I'M WITH YOU?

00:33.667 --> 00:35.375
OK. (CHUCKLES)

00:36.834 --> 00:38.500
HOW'S WORK GOIN', PACE?

00:38.500 --> 00:40.959
UH, IT'S GOING
REALLY WELL,
THANK YOU.

00:40.959 --> 00:42.750
I GOT A PROMOTION,
ACTUALLY.

00:42.750 --> 00:45.500
REALLY? TO WHAT?

00:45.500 --> 00:46.750
I...DON'T KNOW.

00:46.750 --> 00:48.333
THERE'S NO TITLE,
BUT I GET AN OFFICE,

00:48.333 --> 00:50.750
AND, UH,
I GET A SECRETARY.
THAT'S KIND OF COOL.

00:50.750 --> 00:52.083
OOH!
YEAH.

00:52.083 --> 00:54.375
FANCY.

00:54.375 --> 00:57.333
YOU CERTAINLY WON'T
WANT TO TALK TO ME
AFTER TONIGHT, SO...

00:57.333 --> 01:00.542
YOU SEE, I KNEW
YOU WOULD UNDERSTAND.

01:00.542 --> 01:03.000
DON'T KICK A GIRL
WHEN SHE'S DOWN.

01:03.000 --> 01:04.834
YOU KNOW,
I'M STRAPPED FOR CASH,

01:04.834 --> 01:07.375
AND THEY CUT MY HOURS
BECAUSE EVERYONE'S
ON SPRING BREAK,

01:07.375 --> 01:09.083
DRINKING ELSEWHERE.

01:09.083 --> 01:11.667
I GUESS THAT MEANS
YOU'RE FREE FOR DINNER
NEXT SATURDAY.

01:13.000 --> 01:16.041
WELL, ANYTHING
FOR A FREE MEAL.

01:16.041 --> 01:20.000
CLASSY LADY LIKE YOU,
I MIGHT EVEN THROW IN
A FREE DESSERT.

01:20.000 --> 01:22.708
YOU MUST BE SERIOUS
ABOUT ME.

01:30.750 --> 01:32.375
OK, WELL...

01:32.375 --> 01:33.583
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

01:33.583 --> 01:34.917
I THINK
THAT'S MY CUE.

01:34.917 --> 01:36.250
I'M JUST GONNA...
OK.

01:36.250 --> 01:37.667
CUT MY LOSSES.

01:39.125 --> 01:41.083
UM...

01:41.083 --> 01:42.875
I'LL HAVE MY SECRETARY
CALL YOU ABOUT DINNER.

01:42.875 --> 01:45.375
PACEY, I HAD
A LOVELY TIME.

01:47.375 --> 01:48.291
SO DID I.

01:49.291 --> 01:50.542
GOOD NIGHT.

01:50.542 --> 01:52.083
GOOD NIGHT.

02:56.959 --> 02:58.166
(GROANS)

02:58.166 --> 02:59.458
MORNIN', SUNSHINE.

03:00.208 --> 03:02.000
MMM...

03:02.000 --> 03:03.166
WHERE'S GRAMS?

03:03.166 --> 03:06.291
SHE'S DOWNSTAIRS,
STIRRING PORRIDGE.

03:06.291 --> 03:09.000
MMM. REALLY?

03:09.959 --> 03:11.458
SHALL WE, THEN?

03:11.458 --> 03:13.583
SHALL WE WHAT?

03:16.542 --> 03:19.000
OH. (CHUCKLES)

03:19.000 --> 03:21.291
SHALL WE THAT.

03:21.291 --> 03:22.542
YEAH, THAT.

03:22.542 --> 03:26.041
YEAH. NAH.

03:26.041 --> 03:27.667
NO?

03:27.667 --> 03:29.542
NO.

03:29.542 --> 03:31.250
I'M NOT REALLY
IN THE MOOD.

03:31.250 --> 03:33.959
MOOD? WHO NEEDS MOOD?

03:35.667 --> 03:36.750
WHAT?

03:36.750 --> 03:38.208
NOTHING A LITTLE
TOOTHPASTE WON'T FIX.

03:38.208 --> 03:40.000
OH.

03:40.000 --> 03:42.291
WELL, FINE.
THEN DON'T KISS ME.
SEE IF I CARE.

03:44.041 --> 03:45.959
NOT SO SEXY
WHEN YOU'RE POUTING.

03:51.208 --> 03:54.208
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY
OF THESE WERE IN HERE
WHEN I BOUGHT THEM?

03:54.208 --> 03:55.583
12.
MM-HMM.

03:55.583 --> 03:57.041
KNOW HOW MANY
ARE IN HERE NOW?

03:57.041 --> 03:58.500
12.

04:00.750 --> 04:03.208
WE HAVEN'T HAD SEX
IN A WEEK, JEN.

04:03.208 --> 04:05.041
THAT'S HARDLY TRUE.

04:05.041 --> 04:08.041
NOT SINCE GRAMS WENT TO BINGO.
THAT WAS A WEEK AGO TODAY.

04:08.041 --> 04:10.000
WHAT AM I,
SEX ON A STICK?

04:10.000 --> 04:11.917
I'M NOT A BOY.
I DON'T HAVE...

04:11.917 --> 04:14.208
THE SAME KIND
OF SEX DRIVE
THAT YOU DO,

04:14.208 --> 04:15.708
ALL RIGHT?

04:15.708 --> 04:17.416
NOT TO MENTION
THE FACT THAT I--

04:17.416 --> 04:18.750
I LIVE
IN MORTAL TERROR

04:18.750 --> 04:19.916
OF MY GRAMS WALKING
IN ON US

04:19.916 --> 04:21.416
IN THE MIDDLE OF
SOME UNGODLY ACT.

04:21.416 --> 04:23.250
SO MAYBE THAT HELPS
YOU TO UNDERSTAND

04:23.250 --> 04:26.375
WHY I'M NOT
JUMPING YOUR BONES
EVERY CHANCE I GET.

04:26.375 --> 04:29.917
HMM. WOW. THEN IT'S TRUE
WHAT THEY SAY.

04:29.917 --> 04:31.041
WHAT?

04:31.041 --> 04:32.041
ONCE YOU START DATING,

04:32.041 --> 04:33.667
THE SEX GOES
RIGHT OUT THE WINDOW.

04:33.667 --> 04:35.417
YOU ARE SUCH
A DRAMA QUEEN.

04:35.417 --> 04:37.083
(LAUGHS)

04:37.083 --> 04:39.750
YOU KNOW, THERE ARE
OTHER WAYS FOR US
TO BE INTIMATE.

04:42.417 --> 04:44.834
I'M ALL FOR THAT STUFF.

04:44.834 --> 04:46.542
YEAH? SO AM I.

04:46.542 --> 04:47.834
WELL, COME ON.

04:54.250 --> 04:56.083
HMM.

04:56.083 --> 04:58.458
IS THIS WHAT YOU WERE
TALKING ABOUT--SNUGGLING?

04:58.458 --> 05:00.166
MMM. YEAH.

05:02.959 --> 05:05.458
WHAT DID YOU THINK
I WAS TALKING ABOUT?

05:07.625 --> 05:09.458
NOTHING.

05:20.792 --> 05:21.750
JO.

05:21.750 --> 05:23.250
OHH!

05:23.250 --> 05:24.458
HI!

05:24.458 --> 05:26.291
TO WHAT DO I OWE
THIS HONOR?

05:26.291 --> 05:28.458
I--I BROUGHT YOU
AN OFFICE-WARMING GIFT.

05:28.458 --> 05:30.667
YOU WON'T GET IN TROUBLE
FOR HAVING VISITORS,
WILL YOU?

05:30.667 --> 05:33.291
NO, NO. NOT IF YOU STOP
DISTRACTING THE BOYS.

05:33.291 --> 05:35.667
YOU WANT TO STEP
INTO MY OFFICE?

05:35.667 --> 05:37.959
HOW PROFESSIONAL.

05:37.959 --> 05:39.667
SO, EVERYONE'S
JUST ON THE PHONE.

05:39.667 --> 05:41.000
IS THIS WHAT
YOU DO ALL DAY?

05:41.000 --> 05:42.834
IT'S A LITTLE MORE
COMPLICATED THAN THAT.

05:42.834 --> 05:44.667
LET ME GRAB THOSE.
THANKS, TOM.

05:44.667 --> 05:46.667
SO, WHAT MAKES YOU
SO BUSY NOW

05:46.667 --> 05:48.333
THAT YOU NEED
AN ASSISTANT?

05:48.333 --> 05:49.708
I DON'T KNOW,

05:49.708 --> 05:52.542
BUT TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,
SHE KIND OF FREAKS ME OUT.

05:52.542 --> 05:53.542
MARCY?

05:53.542 --> 05:54.959
HI.

05:54.959 --> 05:56.500
I'D LIKE TO INTRODUCE YOU
TO MY FRIEND JO.

05:56.500 --> 05:57.792
NICE TO MEET YOU.

05:57.792 --> 05:59.500
F.Y.I. FOR YOU,
MR. WITTER,

05:59.500 --> 06:00.959
THE MEETING'S BEEN
PUSHED TO 3:00,

06:00.959 --> 06:02.375
AND MR. RINALDI'S
IN YOUR OFFICE.

06:02.375 --> 06:04.708
AND WHEN YOU
HAVE A MOMENT,
I'D LIKE A WORD.

06:04.708 --> 06:05.708
A WORD?

06:05.708 --> 06:07.792
DON'T PATRONIZE ME,
MR. WITTER.

06:07.792 --> 06:09.625
I'M SORRY, MA'AM. I--

06:09.625 --> 06:11.834
YOU CAN TALK NOW
IF YOU LIKE.

06:11.834 --> 06:13.792
FINE, MR. WITTER.
IF YOU MUST KNOW,

06:13.792 --> 06:15.166
MR. RINALDI FIRED ME,

06:15.166 --> 06:17.208
AND I'LL BE LEAVING
AT THE END OF THE DAY.

06:17.208 --> 06:20.041
(SIGHS)

06:21.708 --> 06:23.834
JUST BREAKIN' IT IN
FOR YOU.

06:26.166 --> 06:28.583
OH, WHO'S THE LOOKER?

06:31.250 --> 06:32.708
YOU DO REALIZE

06:32.708 --> 06:34.250
THAT I'M STANDING
RIGHT HERE?

06:34.250 --> 06:36.875
AND YOU DO REALIZE
THAT WAS A COMPLIMENT,
RIGHT?

06:36.875 --> 06:38.708
(CHUCKLES UNCOMFORTABLY)
RICH,

06:38.708 --> 06:39.708
THIS IS JOEY.

06:39.708 --> 06:41.542
JOEY, YOU
REMEMBER RICH.

06:41.542 --> 06:44.917
AND, RICH,
WHY IS IT, EXACTLY,
YOU FIRED MY SECRETARY?

06:44.917 --> 06:47.667
WELL, UH, SHE TRIED
TO KICK ME OUT
OF YOUR OFFICE.

06:47.667 --> 06:49.166
WELL, DOESN'T THAT
DESERVE A RAISE?

06:49.166 --> 06:52.000
YEAH, WELL,
I DIDN'T LIKE
HER ATTITUDE, WITTER,

06:52.000 --> 06:54.708
OR THE CUT OF HER JIB,
FOR THAT MATTER.
(CHUCKLES)

06:54.708 --> 06:55.917
YOU CAN JUST
FIRE SOMEBODY

06:55.917 --> 06:57.917
BECAUSE YOU DON'T LIKE
THE WAY THEY LOOK?

06:57.917 --> 06:59.417
ISN'T THAT
DISCRIMINATION?

06:59.417 --> 07:01.583
IS SHE  HUMAN RESOURCES?

07:01.583 --> 07:03.625
NO. NO, NO.
SHE'S MY, UH...

07:03.625 --> 07:05.083
FRIEND OF MINE.

07:05.083 --> 07:07.125
OH.

07:07.125 --> 07:09.917
SO, UH, WHY AREN'T YOU
IN SCHOOL TODAY?

07:09.917 --> 07:11.083
I'M ON SPRING BREAK.

07:11.083 --> 07:13.208
WHAT DO YOU DO
9 TO 5, JOHNNY?

07:13.208 --> 07:15.375
JOEY.

07:15.375 --> 07:17.875
NOTHING AT THE MOMENT.
UM...

07:17.875 --> 07:21.917
I SAY YOU SPEND
THE NEXT 2 WEEKS
FILLING IN HERE.

07:21.917 --> 07:24.041
YOU KNOW HOW TO PLAY
OFFICE, RIGHT?

07:24.041 --> 07:27.250
WHY DON'T YOU
SET THAT UP, WITTER.

07:27.250 --> 07:28.583
HMM.

07:28.583 --> 07:31.083
HE'S KIDDING, RIGHT?

07:31.083 --> 07:34.708
RICH? NO, HE DOESN'T
REALLY HAVE MUCH
OF A SENSE OF HUMOR.

07:34.708 --> 07:37.083
WELL, HOW MUCH
DOES IT PAY?

07:37.083 --> 07:39.959
I DON'T KNOW.
I THINK IT'S, LIKE,
600 BUCKS A WEEK.

07:39.959 --> 07:42.291
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

07:42.291 --> 07:44.625
WOULD YOU ACTUALLY
WANT TO DO IT?

07:44.625 --> 07:45.834
WELL, YOU HAVE TO
ADMIT, PACE,

07:45.834 --> 07:47.625
I MEAN,
IT IS PERFECT TIMING.

07:47.625 --> 07:48.834
I'M BROKE.

07:48.834 --> 07:50.291
WE NEVER SEE
EACH OTHER ANYMORE.

07:50.291 --> 07:51.875
YEAH, BUT HANGIN' OUT
BY THE COFFEE MACHINE

07:51.875 --> 07:53.083
IS NOT EXACTLY A DATE,
NOW, IS IT?

07:53.083 --> 07:55.458
WHO'S KIDDING WHO, PACE?

07:55.458 --> 07:59.083
NOW, WE BOTH KNOW
THAT THE BOSS

07:59.083 --> 08:01.959
DOESN'T HANG OUT
BY THE COFFEE MACHINE.

08:01.959 --> 08:03.792
THAT WOULD BE
THE ASSISTANT'S JOB.

08:03.792 --> 08:05.792
AND YOU'RE SURE
YOU'D BE COMFORTABLE

08:05.792 --> 08:08.750
WITH THE WHOLE
BOSS/SECRETARY
POWER RELATIONSHIP?

08:08.750 --> 08:11.625
WE BOTH KNOW
WHO'S BOSS HERE.

08:12.959 --> 08:14.125
(CHUCKLES)

08:15.542 --> 08:17.125
WELL, OK, YEAH.
I MEAN,

08:17.125 --> 08:18.959
WHAT'S THE WORST THAT
COULD HAPPEN, RIGHT?

08:18.959 --> 08:21.625
BARRING ME TAKING OVER
THE COMPANY, NOTHING.

08:21.625 --> 08:24.000
HOW FUN IS THIS GONNA BE!

08:31.041 --> 08:32.707
IT'S ABOUT A LOT OF THINGS,

08:32.707 --> 08:34.166
BUT MORE THAN ANYTHING,

08:34.166 --> 08:36.417
IT'S ABOUT WHAT
IT FEELS LIKE TO BE 15...

08:36.417 --> 08:38.291
THAT TIME IN YOUR LIFE
WHEN EVERYTHING'S NEW

08:38.291 --> 08:40.500
AND YOU'RE CONSTANTLY
ON THE EDGE OF A BROKEN HEART.

08:40.500 --> 08:43.625
I MEAN, IT SHOULD BE STYLIZED
AND OPERATIC AND...

08:43.625 --> 08:44.792
AND...

08:44.792 --> 08:47.708
I'D LIKE TO DIRECT IT.

08:47.708 --> 08:49.000
(CHUCKLES)
WHOA, JUNIOR.

08:49.000 --> 08:50.667
LET'S NOT GET
AHEAD OF OURSELVES.

08:50.667 --> 08:52.834
WALK BEFORE YOU RUN.

08:52.834 --> 08:54.458
OK.

08:54.458 --> 08:55.667
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

08:55.667 --> 08:58.166
I LIKE IT.

08:58.166 --> 08:59.041
I DO.

08:59.041 --> 09:01.250
AND I THINK YOUR PASSION
FOR IT IS GREAT.

09:01.250 --> 09:03.166
IT'S JUST...

09:03.166 --> 09:04.875
WHAT?

09:04.875 --> 09:06.166
IT'S A LITTLE SOFT.

09:06.166 --> 09:08.208
AND IN CASE
YOU HAVEN'T NOTICED,

09:08.208 --> 09:09.708
WE DON'T REALLY DO
SOFT AROUND HERE.

09:09.708 --> 09:11.375
WE DO EXPLOITATION.

09:11.375 --> 09:14.500
LARRY LEARNED
EVERYTHING HE KNOWS
FROM ROGER CORMAN.

09:14.500 --> 09:16.041
YOU COULD PITCH HIM
CITIZEN KANE,

09:16.041 --> 09:18.000
AND UNLESS
THERE'S A MINIMUM
OF 3 NUDE SCENES,

09:18.000 --> 09:19.750
HE'D GIVE YOU A LOOK
LIKE HE JUST
SMELLED A FART.

09:19.750 --> 09:20.750
OK. THAT'S ALL
WELL AND GOOD,

09:20.750 --> 09:22.750
BUT I'M NOT SURE
I KNOW HOW TO
MAKE THAT MOVIE.

09:22.750 --> 09:23.708
MY ADVICE TO YOU...

09:23.708 --> 09:24.834
IS TO PLAY UP THE SEX.

09:24.834 --> 09:26.500
HE'LL UNDERSTAND THAT.

09:26.500 --> 09:28.750
WHAT MAKES THIS PITCH
SO INTERESTING AND UNIQUE

09:28.750 --> 09:30.750
IS THE FACT THAT
IT'S THIS EPIC LOVE STORY

09:30.750 --> 09:31.875
WITHOUT THE SEX.

09:31.875 --> 09:34.166
I'LL LET YOU IN
ON A LITTLE SECRET.

09:34.166 --> 09:37.166
LARRY NEWMAN IS
THE HORNIEST MAN ALIVE,

09:37.166 --> 09:38.875
A WORLD-CLASS PERVERT.

09:38.875 --> 09:39.917
HE'S ON HIS THIRD WIFE.

09:39.917 --> 09:41.417
SHE'S 23...

09:41.417 --> 09:43.166
AND DONE A LOT OF WORK
IN THE VALLEY,

09:43.166 --> 09:44.417
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

09:44.417 --> 09:45.917
WHICH DOESN'T SEEM
TO STOP HIM

09:45.917 --> 09:47.917
FROM COVETING MY RACK,
MIND YOU.

09:47.917 --> 09:49.792
(CHUCKLES)
I'M SO SORRY.

09:49.792 --> 09:52.083
THAT MUST BE TERRIBLE
TO WORK IN AN ENVIRONMENT
LIKE THAT.

09:52.083 --> 09:54.041
PLEASE.

09:54.041 --> 09:57.041
YOU'VE BEEN STARING
AT THE TWINS FOR
THE PAST 20 MINUTES.

09:57.041 --> 09:58.875
I...

09:58.875 --> 10:00.417
NOT THAT I MIND,
OF COURSE.

10:00.417 --> 10:02.959
THEY ARE FANTASTIC

10:02.959 --> 10:04.542
AND WORTH EVERY PENNY.

10:06.250 --> 10:08.041
WHAT'S MY POINT?

10:08.041 --> 10:10.250
I DON'T KNOW.

10:10.250 --> 10:11.917
MY POINT IS...

10:11.917 --> 10:14.041
IF YOU WANT TO MAKE
A MOVIE WITH US,

10:14.041 --> 10:16.250
FIND A WAY
TO TELL YOUR STORY

10:16.250 --> 10:19.125
WHILE STILL APPEALING
TO THE LOWEST COMMON
DENOMINATOR.

10:19.125 --> 10:20.750
PITCH LARRY
THE SAME THING
YOU PITCHED ME,

10:20.750 --> 10:24.083
ONLY THROW IN...
A STRIPPER, A 3-WAY,

10:24.083 --> 10:27.083
OR LIKE AN AFFAIR
WITH A TEACHER
OR SOMETHING.

10:31.375 --> 10:33.083
I CAN DO THAT.

10:40.333 --> 10:43.250
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

10:45.291 --> 10:47.291
HELP LINE.
THIS IS JEN SPEAKING.

10:50.083 --> 10:52.458
ARE YOU SURE THAT THAT'S
ACTUALLY A PROBLEM?

10:52.458 --> 10:55.125
BECAUSE
SPEAKING AS A GIRL

10:55.125 --> 10:56.875
WHOSE BOYFRIEND
WANTS TO COPULATE

10:56.875 --> 10:58.625
EVERY WAKING MOMENT
OF THE DAY,

10:58.625 --> 11:00.458
I WOULD ACTUALLY
WELCOME THE BREAK.

11:00.458 --> 11:02.500
I MEAN, I APPRECIATE
THE ENTHUSIASM.

11:02.500 --> 11:05.500
IT'S JUST IT'S--IT'S
A LITTLE EXHAUSTING.

11:05.500 --> 11:06.959
THIS POSITION, THAT POSITION,

11:06.959 --> 11:08.458
"YOU WANT MY LEGS WHERE?"

11:10.166 --> 11:12.375
I MEAN, I CAN'T EVEN
WEAR A SKIRT ANYMORE

11:12.375 --> 11:16.000
WITHOUT HIM TAKING IT
AS AN INVITATION
TO HIKE IT UP.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.875
HEY, WITTER,
NICELY DONE.

11:18.875 --> 11:20.667
NICELY DONE,
INDEED.

11:20.667 --> 11:22.500
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKIN' ABOUT?

11:22.500 --> 11:24.041
THE NEW HIRE.

11:24.041 --> 11:25.375
OH. JOEY.

11:26.208 --> 11:27.375
HEY, JOE.

11:30.291 --> 11:33.583
OH. MORNING, PACE.

11:33.583 --> 11:35.208
MORNING.

11:38.708 --> 11:40.583
EXCUSE ME.

11:42.333 --> 11:44.166
ARE THESE GUYS
BOTHERIN' YOU?

11:44.166 --> 11:46.500
NO. THEY MAY BE TRYING TO,

11:46.500 --> 11:48.166
BUT I CAN'T EXACTLY TELL.

11:48.166 --> 11:50.750
DID ANY OF YOU
GO TO COLLEGE?

11:50.750 --> 11:52.417
WE'RE JUST SHOWIN'
HER THE ROPES, PACEY.

11:52.417 --> 11:54.208
ARE YOU COMFORTABLE,
JOEY?

11:54.208 --> 11:55.834
I MEAN, THIS SEEMS
A LITTLE HIGH.

11:56.708 --> 11:57.708
OH. OH, WHOA.

11:57.708 --> 11:59.041
(CHUCKLES)

11:59.041 --> 12:01.583
THAT'S...SUPER.
THANK YOU.

12:01.583 --> 12:03.875
WELL, GREAT.
I'M GLAD WE GOT
THAT ALL FIXED UP.

12:03.875 --> 12:05.500
BUT SEEING AS THIS
IS MY  SECRETARY,

12:05.500 --> 12:08.417
WHY DON'T YOU GUYS
GO BACK TO YOUR--
AHEM!

12:08.417 --> 12:10.000
OFFICE TEMP--
IT'S NOT IMPORTANT
RIGHT NOW.

12:10.000 --> 12:11.208
WHAT'S IMPORTANT--

12:11.208 --> 12:12.542
SHE'S NOT GONNA
BE HERE LONG,

12:12.542 --> 12:13.792
SO DON'T GET
TOO ATTACHED.

12:14.875 --> 12:16.458
BYE-BYE.

12:20.333 --> 12:21.875
NEANDER-CREEPS.

12:21.875 --> 12:23.625
SORRY ABOUT THAT.

12:30.708 --> 12:32.125
WHAT IS THIS?

12:32.125 --> 12:35.375
OH. WELL, THAT'S YOUR
OFFICE-WARMING GIFT.

12:35.375 --> 12:37.000
YOU FORGOT TO OPEN IT
YESTERDAY.

12:37.000 --> 12:39.208
I THOUGHT SINCE NOW
YOU'RE A TRUE PROFESSIONAL

12:39.208 --> 12:40.959
AND YOU HAVE AN OFFICE
OF YOUR OWN,

12:40.959 --> 12:43.750
THAT YOU DESERVE
POINTLESS GADGETS
TO STICK ON YOUR DESK.

12:43.750 --> 12:44.959
WELL, THANK YOU,
MISS POTTER.

